E2%80%9D%20bad%20craftsman%20always%20blames%20his%20tools%20for%20poor%20outcome.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697796044000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19181855%2Fimage-1410.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fyoutube-warning-tags-rahul-priyanka-congress-criticism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20social%20media%20platform%20added%20%E2%80%9Cself%20harm%E2%80%9D%20tags%20to%20a%20video%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra's%20speeches%20in%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20Mulugu%20on%20October%2018.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fyoutube-warning-tags-rahul-priyanka-congress-criticism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%20Govt%20Order%20Banning%20Sharing%20of%20Media%20Related%20to%20Violence%20Potentially%20Unconstitutional%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30163218%2FFwqAt6VXsAIGp1_.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Manipur%20Home%20Department%20notified%20Order%20No.%20H-3608%2F2%2F2023-HD-HD%C2%A0%20on%20October%2011%2C%202023%20%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-photo-video-footage-ban%5C%22%3Erestrains%20the%20sharing%20of%20videos%2Fimages%20depicting%20acts%20of%20violence%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20(IFF)%20believes%20this%20order%20infringes%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20limits%20journalistic%20freedom%20and%20hampers%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20essential%20information.%20We%20wrote%20to%20the%20Manipur%20Home%20Department%20to%20reconsider%20these%20restrictions%2C%20citing%20constitutional%20violations%20and%20potential%20dangers%20to%20citizens%E2%80%99%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Should%20You%20Care%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EManipur%20has%20been%20under%20an%20information%20blockade%20since%20May%202023.%20This%20order%20strengthens%20the%20blockade%20by%20severely%20restricting%20the%20essential%20journalistic%20freedoms%20of%20media%20and%20news%20professionals%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20of%20all%20residents%20of%20Manipur.%20Further%2C%20the%20circulation%20of%20information%20via%20visual%20media%20equips%20people%20to%20assess%20their%20immediate%20surroundings%20better%20and%20travel%20safely%20in%20their%20vicinity%20for%20access%20to%20resources.%20This%20order%20virtually%20impedes%20the%20capacity%20of%20a%20person%20to%20receive%20information%20pertaining%20to%20the%20violence%20taking%20place%20in%20their%20vicinity%2C%20and%20thereby%20places%20them%20in%20potential%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmidst%20the%20ongoing%20internet%20blackout%2C%20there%20comes%20a%20new%20restriction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOwing%20to%20the%20ongoing%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20between%20communities%2C%20the%20state%20has%20been%20subjected%20to%20multiple%20internet%20shutdowns%20in%20the%20year%202023.%20The%20first%20shutdown%20was%20imposed%20on%20May%203%2C%202023%2C%20and%20the%20latest%20internet%20shutdown%20order%20was%20issued%20on%20October%201%2C%202023%2C%20which%20is%20still%20ongoing.%20Amidst%20the%20communication%20challenges%20already%20existing%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20blackout%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20Manipur%20decided%20to%20issue%20yet%20another%20order%20that%20explicitly%20bars%20the%20sharing%20of%20videos%2Fimages%20portraying%20violent%20incidents%20in%20the%20state%20which%20aims%20to%20curb%20violence.%20IFF%20argues%20that%20this%20order%20oversteps%20constitutional%20boundaries%20and%20jeopardises%20essential%20freedoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20prohibits%20the%20circulation%20of%20any%20images%2Fvideos%20that%20depict%20violent%20activities%2C%20such%20as%20causing%20injury%20to%20the%20body%20and%2For%20damaging%20public%20or%20private%20property%2C%20via%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20explicitly%20mentioning%20WhatsApp%2C%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20Twitter%2C%20etc.%20Though%20the%20stated%20intention%20of%20this%20order%20is%20to%20bring%20%E2%80%9Cnormalcy%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20State%2C%20the%20order%20states%20that%20the%20circulation%20of%20the%20above%20via%20electronic%20equipment%20like%20mobile%20phones%2C%20computers%2C%20tablets%20etc.%20or%20even%20the%20possession%20of%20such%20material%20will%20result%20in%20%E2%80%9Cappropriate%20legal%20action%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20mandates%20that%20the%20violation%20of%20its%20provisions%20will%20result%20in%20the%20person%20being%20%E2%80%9Cbooked%20and%20prosecuted%E2%80%9D%3B%20thereby%20severely%20limiting%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20by%20way%20of%20not%20making%20other%20citizens%20aware%20of%20a%20potentially%20hostile%20environment%2C%20directly%20contravening%20the%20right%20to%20life%20by%20putting%20the%20people%20in%20harm%E2%80%99s%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20order%20is%20potentially%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20Manipur%20(Home)%20enlisting%20our%20concerns%20and%20the%20impact%20it%20could%20have%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20rights%20and%20digital%20liberties.%20We%20highlighted%20the%20following%2C%20among%20other%2C%20concerns%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuppression%20of%20Legitimate%20Journalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20This%20measure%20could%20significantly%20suppress%20legitimate%20journalism.%20By%20restricting%20the%20dissemination%20of%20information%2C%20it%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20severely%20limit%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20pertinent%20news%20and%20crucial%20insights.%20Consequently%2C%20it%20could%20hinder%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20gain%20a%20comprehensive%20understanding%20of%20the%20current%20situation%20and%20make%20informed%20decisions.%20Moreover%2C%20this%20restriction%20could%20have%20broader%20implications%20for%20communal%20violence%20investigations%2C%20where%20the%20availability%20of%20crucial%20evidence%20may%20be%20stifled%20due%20to%20limited%20investigative%20resources.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EViolation%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Free%20Speech%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Beyond%20its%20effect%20on%20journalism%2C%20this%20measure%20has%20serious%20implications%20for%20free%20speech.%20It%20imposes%20prior%20restraint%20by%20engaging%20in%20pre-censorship%20and%20effectively%20prohibiting%20the%20sharing%20of%20videos%20or%20images%20before%20these%20events%20transpire.%20This%20act%20contradicts%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20which%20safeguards%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression.%20This%20was%20affirmed%20by%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Brij%20Bhushan%20vs%20The%20State%20Of%20Delhi%2C%20which%20found%20that%20prior%20restraint%20on%20speech%20based%20on%20presumption%20is%20fundamentally%20unconstitutional.%20Furthermore%2C%20this%20measure%20stifles%20the%20marketplace%20of%20ideas%2C%20as%20limiting%20discourse%20can%20undermine%20the%20very%20foundations%20of%20a%20democratic%20society.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EOverbreadth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20measure%E2%80%99s%20overbroad%20language%20adds%20another%20layer%20of%20concern.%20It%20prohibits%20the%20sharing%20of%20media%20content%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20may%20aggravate%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20in%20the%20State.%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20notably%20vague%20and%2C%20when%20scrutinised%2C%20does%20not%20fall%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20specific%20legal%20provisions%20under%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20or%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act.%20Further%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3EShreya%20Singhal%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20rectified%20a%20pre-existing%20provision%20that%20was%20overbroad%20and%20impermissibly%20restricted%20free%20speech%2C%20aligning%20it%20more%20closely%20with%20constitutional%20standards.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EViolation%20of%20Article%2021%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Finally%2C%20the%20measure%20is%20violative%20of%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%20The%20punitive%20consequences%20listed%20in%20this%20measure%20serve%20as%20a%20deterrent%20for%20the%20public%20to%20share%20information%20and%20be%20aware%2C%20consequently%20compromising%20their%20ability%20to%20protect%20their%20own%20lives.%20The%20sharing%20of%20media%20content%20mentioned%20in%20the%20order%20can%20be%20vital%20for%20the%20citizens%20of%20Manipur%20to%20exercise%20vigilance%20in%20terms%20of%20location%2C%20time%2C%20and%20the%20general%20ambience%20of%20areas%2C%20thus%20enabling%20them%20to%20safeguard%20themselves.%20In%20essence%2C%20this%20measure%20not%20only%20hinders%20access%20to%20information%20but%20also%20endangers%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20citizens%20of%20Manipur.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20concern%20over%20the%20Manipur%20government%E2%80%99s%20recent%20order%20reflects%20a%20broader%20debate%20on%20balancing%20security%20measures%20with%20citizens%E2%80%99%20constitutional%20rights.%20As%20digital%20rights%20become%20increasingly%20vital%20in%20our%20society%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20navigate%20these%20complexities%20with%20careful%20consideration%20for%20individual%20freedoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20advocated%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20residents%20of%20Manipur%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20internet%20shutdowns%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fmanipur-online-censorship%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20hre