n%20to%20the%20world.%20Still.%20Still%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFresh%20from%20a%20whirlwind%20trip%20to%20Israel%20this%20week%2C%20Biden%20wants%20to%20win%20over%20war-weary%20voters%20and%20hardline%20Republicans%20as%20he%20ramps%20up%20his%202024%20reelection%20bid.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20is%20said%20to%20be%20teeing%20up%20a%20huge%20request%20to%20Congress%20for%20a%20%24100%20billion%20package%20that%20would%20include%20funding%20for%20Israel%20in%20its%20war%20with%20Hamas%20and%20also%20for%20Ukraine's%20battle%20against%20Russian%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETying%20together%20two%20conflicts%20an%20ocean%20away%20from%20the%20United%20States%20is%20a%20bid%20by%20Biden%20to%20frame%20them%20as%20part%20of%20a%20bigger%20struggle%20to%20shape%20the%20world%20order%20and%20protect%20Americans%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E-%20Somber%20setting%20of%20Oval%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPresidents%20traditionally%20reserve%20speeches%20from%20the%20solemn%20setting%20of%20the%20Oval%20Office%20for%20moments%20of%20key%20national%20significance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBiden's%20only%20previous%20address%20from%20there%20was%20in%20June%20when%20he%20hailed%20a%20deal%20with%20Congress%20to%20avert%20what%20would%20have%20been%20a%20catastrophic%20US%20debt%20default.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20Congress%20has%20now%20been%20paralyzed%20for%20more%20than%20two%20weeks%20as%20divided%20Republicans%2C%20who%20control%20the%20majority%20in%20the%20House%2C%20fail%20repeatedly%20to%20agree%20on%20electing%20a%20House%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHard-right%20Republicans%2C%20and%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20voters%2C%20are%20also%20strongly%20opposed%20to%20adding%20to%20the%20%2443.9%20billion%20in%20security%20assistance%20that%20the%20United%20States%20has%20committed%20to%20Ukraine%20since%20Moscow%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20in%20February%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUS%20media%20reported%20that%20Friday's%20package%