rpts%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHannity%20and%20Carlson%20were%20both%20hosts%20at%20Fox%20News%20until%20Carlson%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftucker-carlson-out-at-fox-news-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebooted%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20network%20in%20April.%20Carlson%20joined%20Fox%20in%202009%2C%20and%20started%20hosting%20his%20own%20talk%20show%20on%20the%20network%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHannity%20got%20his%20start%20at%20Fox%20much%20earlier%2C%20joining%20the%20network%20in%201996%20and%20eventually%20hosting%20his%20own%20show%20in%202009.%20Romney%2C%20as%20a%20high-profile%20GOP%20lawmaker%2C%20spoke%20frequently%20on%20Hannity's%20TV%20and%20radio%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20then-presidential%20candidate%20Donald%20Trump%20rose%20in%20political%20influence%2C%20both%20hosts%20gravitated%20to%20his%20far-right%20rhetoric%20and%20conspiracy%20theories.%20That%20put%20them%20increasingly%20at%20odds%20with%20Romney%2C%20who%20decried%20the%20MAGA%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20Romney%20suspected%20Hannity%20was%20being%20influenced%20by%20Carlson's%20style%2C%20Coppins'%20book%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20in%20the%20same%20vein%20as%20Tucker.%20Just%20not%20as%20effective%20as%20Tucker%2C%26quot%3B%20Romney%20said%2C%20per%20the%20book.%20%26quot%3BTucker's%20smart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Fox%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftucker-carlson-ratings-claim-fox-news-semafor-ben-smith-interview-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECarlson%20had%20been%20a%20star%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20setting%20a%20record%20for%20the%20most-watched%20host%20in%20US%20history.%20He%20averaged%204.5%20million%20views%20per%20quarter%20when%20he%20earned%20that%20accolade%20in%20April%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20detailed%20in%20Coppins'%20book%2C%20Romney%20lamented%20what%20he%20saw%20as%20Carlson%20leading%20the%20charge