3E%C2%A0and%20that%20interview%2C%20I%20found%20that%20it%20began%20to%20flow%20again.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20happy%20that%20I%E2%80%99ve%20been%20able%20to%20write%20this%20book%2C%20which%20will%20come%20out%20in%20the%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWas%20there%20anything%20that%20helped%20you%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYou%20know%2C%20just%20practice.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20been%20doing%20this%20job%20a%20long%20time.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20gets%20you%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20talk%20about%20your%20current%20book%2C%20%E2%80%9CVictory%20City%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20was%20published%20this%20year.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20fictionalised%20telling%20of%20the%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20the%20medieval%20city%20of%20Bisnaga%20in%20southern%20India%2C%20where%20men%20and%20women%20of%20diverse%20faiths%20were%20meant%20to%20be%20equal.%20But%20the%20empire%20perishes%20at%20the%20end%20because%20it%20abandons%20all%20its%20ideals.%20Is%20this%20a%20commentary%20on%20the%20contemporary%20world%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20if%20you%20write%20about%20history%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20also%20writing%20about%20the%20present%20day%20because%20when%20we%20look%20at%20the%20past%2C%20we%20see%20what%20interests%20us%2C%20our%20own%20concerns%20reflected%20in%20earlier%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20really%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20world%20of%20my%20own.%20There%20are%20many%20writers%20who%20have%20done%20this%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20William%20Faulkner%20with%20his%20Yoknapatawpha%2C%20%5BGabriel%5D%20Garcia%20Marquez%20with%20Macondo%2C%20or%20the%20Indian%20writer%20R.%20K.%20Narayan%20with%20Malgudi.%20I%20wanted%20a%20little%20world%20of%20my%20own%2C%20and%20this%20saga%20became%20that%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESome%20critics%20have%20said%20that%20the%20book%20is%20a%20feminist%20novel.%20Was%20that%20your%20intention%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3