%20strange%20because%20writers%20have%20no%20armies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20your%20explanation%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20they%20fear%20alternative%20versions%20of%20the%20world.%20One%20of%20the%20things%20about%20authoritarian%20rule%20is%20it%20also%20imposes%20its%20own%20version%20of%20the%20world%20to%20the%20exclusion%20of%20all%20others.%20Of%20course%2C%20all%20writers%20have%20their%20own%20version%20of%20the%20world%20and%20sometimes%20those%20don%E2%80%99t%20please%20people%20in%20power%2C%20and%20so%20they%20try%C2%A0to%20silence%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAmid%20the%20current%20war%20between%20Hamas%20and%20Israel%2C%20what%20can%20literature%20do%20to%20help%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVery%20little.%20You%20know%2C%20I%C2%A0always%20try%C2%A0not%20to%20overstate%20the%20power%20of%20literature.%20What%20writers%20can%20do%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20and%20what%C2%A0they%20are%20doing%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20to%20try%20and%20articulate%20the%20incredible%20pain%20that%20many%20people%20are%20feeling%20right%20now%20and%20to%20bring%20that%20to%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20attention.%20I%20think%20writers%20everywhere%20are%20doing%20that%20right%20now%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20probably%20the%20best%20we%20can%20do%3A%20articulate%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESo%C2%A0are%20you%20saying%20that%C2%A0words%20in%20this%20situation%20lose%20their%20power%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20just%20think%20there%20are%20things%20that%20words%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%2C%20and%20what%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20is%20stop%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20casualties%20usually%20of%20war%20is%20truth%20because%20people%20start%20presenting%20their%20own%20propaganda%20version%C2%A0of%20events.%C2%A0And%20that%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20when%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20distinguish%20fact%20from%20fiction%20in%20a%20war%20zone.