20therefore%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmisusing%20local%20laws%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20non-profit%20organisations%20like%20Amnesty%20International%20and%20policy%20think%20tanks%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ffatf-probes-india-as-ngos-say-its-misusing-laws-2734023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereports%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFATF%20is%20a%20watchdog%20which%20oversees%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%20implementation%20of%20legal%2C%20regulatory%20and%20operational%20measures%20to%20combat%20money%20laundering%20and%20terror%20financing.%20%3Cspan%3EBut%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%2C%20citing%20two%20officials%20close%20to%20the%20developments%2C%20that%20FATF%20is%20seeking%20to%20look%20at%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20adverse%20impact%20India%E2%80%99s%20laws%20are%20having%20on%20the%20functioning%20of%20non-profit%20organisations%20and%20civil%20society%20groups%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20FATF%20team%20is%20to%20visit%20India%20in%20November%20and%20is%20slated%20to%20catch%20up%20with%20NGOs%20to%20make%20a%20close%20assessment%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20the%20report%20cites%20people%20in%20the%20know%20as%20saying.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20review%20could%20be%20detrimental%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20credibility.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENGOs%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENGOs%20need%20to%20register%20and%20secure%20a%20license%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20Regulation%20Act%20(FCRA)%20to%20be%20able%20to%20receive%20money%20from%20international%20sources%2C%20a%20process%20overseen%20by%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%20(MHA).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Modi%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Famidst-cancellations-of-thousands-of-ngos-licences-ram-mandir-applies-for-fcra-licence%5C%22%3Erecently%20granted%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20FCRA%20licence%20to%20the%20Shri%20Ram%20Janmbhoomi%20Teerth%20Kshetra%2C%20the%20trust%20overseeing%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20its%20approach%20to%20NGOs%20and%20groups%20not%20known%20to%20be%20directly%20under%20its%20control%20has%20been%20under%20the%20scanner.%20Amnesty%20shut%20down%20its%20offices%20in%20India%20in%202020%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cconstant%20harassment%E2%80%9D%20from%20government%20agencies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20revoked%20the%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Research%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20raise%20foreign%20funds.%20The%20Delhi%20high%20court%20had%20to%20intervene%20to%20allow%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20New%20Delhi-based%20think-tank%2C%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20finest%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0access%20to%20use%2025%25%20of%20FCRA%20funds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20BJP%20took%20office%2C%20the%20number%20of%20organisations%20with%20FCRA%20licenses%20has%20declined%20sharply%20and%20critics%20say%20the%20turn%20has%20been%20in%20the%20fortunes%20of%20NGOs%20known%20to%20be%20independent%20or%20not%20toeing%20the%20government%20line.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffcra-licenses-400-ngos-invalid%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%20on%20the%20decline%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20affects%20thousands%20of%20grassroots%20workers%20and%20organisations%20in%20the%20country.%20On%20January%201%2C%202022%2C%20the%20MHA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffcra-licence-revoked-for-6000-entities-including-ima-iit-delhi-jamia-milia%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0that%20nearly%206%2C000%20organisations%20had%20lost%20their%20FCRA%20licenses.%20Before%20that%2C%20in%20December%202016%2C%20the%20FCRA%20licences%20of%20about%2020%2C000%20NGOs%20%E2%80%93%20out%20of%20about%2033%2C000%20that%20had%20this%20license%20%E2%80%93%20were%20cancelled%20for%20alleged%20violations%20of%20the%20Act.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20reports%20that%20in%20a%20statement%20this%20week%2C%20the%20FATF%20said%20that%20it%20had%20started%20a%20%E2%80%9CMutual%20Evaluation%20process%E2%80%9D%20and%20can%E2%80%99t%20comment%20on%20the%20actions%20India%20is%20taking.%20It%20said%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20standards%20%E2%80%9Care%20designed%20to%20ensure%20legitimate%20charitable%20activities%20are%20not%20disrupted%20or%20discouraged.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20unclear%20what%20action%2C%20if%20any%2C%20FATF%20would%20take%20should%20its%20examiners%20find%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20abused%20its%20powers%2C%20reports%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20backsliding%20has%20been%20a%20matter%20recorded%20by%20several%20expert%20groups%20that%20study%20long-term%20trends%20in%20democracy%20globally.%20In%202021%2C%20V-Dem%20or%20Varieties%20of%20Democracy%2C%20categorised%20India%20not%20as%20a%20democracy%20but%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Celectoral%20autocracy.%E2%80%9D%20Freedom%20House%20listed%20India%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpartly%20free.%E2%80%9D%20India%20being%20the%20global%20%E2%80%98Internet%20shutdown%20capital%E2%80%99%20has%20also%20damaged%20its%20reputation%20as%20a%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFATF%20in%20the%20news%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFATF%20puts%20countries%20with%20weak%20terrorist%20financing%20and%20money%20laundering%20provisions%20on%20their%20%E2%80%98grey%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98black%E2%80%99%20lists.%20This%20amounts%20to%20restricting%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20borrowing%20capabilities%20globally.%20Pakistan%20%C8%A7s%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98grey%E2%80%99%20list%20until%20recently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIntriguingly%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20former%20Enforcement%20Director%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20Mishra%20should%20continue%20in%20his%20position%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Edespite%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20strictures%20because%20he%20was%20vital%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20case%20for%20the%20FATF.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgovt-back-in-sc-on-tenure-extension-of-ed-director-court-fixes-hearing-on-july-27%2Farticle67122622.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eapplication%20read%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CUnion%20of%20India%20is%20compelled%20to%20approach%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20extension%20of%20the%20tenure%20of%20Mr.%20Mishra%20up%20to%20October%2015%2C%202023%20in%20view%20of%20the%20ongoing%20FATF%20review%20which%20is%20at%20a%20critical%20stage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fatf-gafi.org%2Fen%2Fhome.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20FATF%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20comprises%2039%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20France%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20China.%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20membership%20was%20suspended%20on%20February%2022%2C%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20ministry%20and%20home%20ministry%20didn%E2%80%99t%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20a%20response.%20It%20also%20notes%20that%20FATF%E2%80%99s%20evaluation%2C%20if%20it%20does%20happen%2C%20would%20be%20a%20first%20as%20there%20%E2%80%9Cis%20no%20precedent%20for%20a%20country%20that%20is%20overzealous%20in%20using%20its%20money%20laundering%20laws%2C%20as%20would%20be%20the%20case%20with%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20month%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffresh-adani-revelations-that-hint-at-r